OL,3,CEx-chief of borders David Neal said he
OL,4,Cwas fired 'for doing his job'
OL,6,FHe was removed from his position last
OL,7,Fweek after he said the Home Office was
OL,8,Fbeing too slow in publishing reports
OL,9,Fby his department.
OL,11,FMr Neal told the Commons Home Affairs
OL,12,FCommittee: "I've been sacked for doing
OL,13,Fmy job.
OL,15,F"I think I've been sacked for doing
OL,16,Fwhat the law asks of me and I've
OL,17,Fbreached, I've fallen down over a
OL,18,Fclause in my employment contract,
OL,19,Fwhich I think is a crying shame."
