OL,3,CEx-chief of borders David Neal said he
OL,4,Cwas fired 'for doing his job'
OL,6,FThe former borders inspector said:
OL,7,F"Worse than that, for my high-
OL,8,Fperforming team of 30 civil servants,
OL,9,Fthe notification that I was sacked was
OL,10,Fin the media before my team or I had
OL,11,Fhad the chance to speak to them, which
OL,12,Fis just shocking. Shocking leadership."
OL,14,FThe defended the professionalism of
OL,15,Fthe Home Office in the wake of Mr
OL,16,FNeal's comments to MPs, telling the PA
OL,17,Fnews agency: "It was disappointing the
OL,18,Fsequence of events that led to me
OL,19,Fasking him to stand down but we have
OL,20,Fremained professional throughout this
OL,21,Fprocess."
